// rcraid backs the root filesystem via an out-of-tree DKMS module. An
// unattended kernel update that changed a kernel API rcraid uses could fail
// to (re)build the module, leaving the new kernel's initramfs without rcraid
// and the machine unbootable — with no operator watching.
//
// This drop-in keeps kernel packages OUT of unattended-upgrades so kernel
// changes are always deliberate. APT merges Package-Blacklist entries from
// every apt.conf.d file, so this appends to (does not replace) the stock
// 50unattended-upgrades list, and survives that package being upgraded.
//
// After you DELIBERATELY update a kernel, run scripts/verify-boot-safety.sh
// and keep a known-good fallback kernel installed before rebooting.
//
// To go back to automatic kernel updates, remove this file.
Unattended-Upgrade::Package-Blacklist {
    "linux-image-";
    "linux-headers-";
    "linux-modules-";
    "linux-generic";
    "linux-lowlatency";
};
